<inglise> COUNCIL DECISION of 26 June 1991 setting up a programme of options specific to the remote and insular nature of Madeira and the Azores (Poseima) (91/315/EEC) </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU OTSUS nr 91/315/EM&Uuml;, millega luuakse Madeira ja Assooride k&otilde;rvalisele asukohale ning saarelisele asendile vastavate valikmeetmete programm (Poseima) 26. juuni 1991 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Articles 43, 113 and 235 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikleid 43, 113 ja 235, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Act of Accession of Spain and Portugal, and in particular Article 234 (3) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Hispaania ja Portugali &uuml;hinemisakti, eriti selle artikli 234 l&otilde;iget 3, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the autonomous Portuguese regions of the Azores and Madeira belong politically and economically to the Community by virtue of the Act of Accession, which did, however, recognize some of their specific characteristics by allowing various isolated exceptions in the application of the common policies; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: Portugali autonoomsed piirkonnad Assoorid ja Madeira kuuluvad poliitiliselt ja majanduslikult &uuml;henduse koosseisu &uuml;hinemisakti alusel, millega on siiski tunnustatud nende m&otilde;ningaid erijooni, lubades erandeid &uuml;histe poliitikate kohaldamisel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Member States, in a joint declaration annexed to the Act of Accession, called on the Community institutions to devote special attention to the development policies of the two archipelagos, 'the object of which is to overcome the handicaps of these regions, which arise from their geographical situation, far away from the mainland of Europe, their physical geographical features, the serious deficiency of infrastructures and their economic backwardness'; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;hinemisaktile lisatud &uuml;hisdeklaratsioonis on liikmesriigid palunud &uuml;henduse institutsioonidel p&ouml;&ouml;rata erilist t&auml;helepanu kahe k&otilde;nealuse saarer&uuml;hma arengupoliitikale, "mille eesm&auml;rgiks on &uuml;le saada nende piirkondade geograafilisest asendist (kaugel Euroopa mandriosast), loodusgeograafilistest erip&auml;radest, t&otilde;sistest infrastruktuurilistest puuduj&auml;&auml;kidest ja majanduslikust mahaj&auml;&auml;musest tulenevatest puuduj&auml;&auml;kidest"; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the European Parliament, in its resolution of 14 April 1989 on Community programmes to help the Portuguese autonomous island regions (1), considered that in view of their island status and highly peripheral situation the Azores and Madeira deserve special treatment from the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa Parlament on oma 14. aprilli 1989. aasta otsuses &uuml;henduse programmide kohta Portugali autonoomsete saarepiirkondade aitamiseks (1) leidnud, et saarelisest ja perifeersest asendist tulenevalt v&auml;&auml;rivad Assoorid ja Madeira &uuml;henduse erire&zcaron;iimi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Azores and Madeira suffer from a serious structural lack of development aggravated by a number of constraints (remoteness, isolation, small size, difficult terrain and climate) whose unchanging nature and combined impact have serious effects on their economic and social development and place these two archipelagos among the least-favoured regions of the Community; whereas these special constraints make it necessary to step up Community support in order to ensure that the Azores and Madeira are fully involved in the dynamic of the internal market; whereas this Community support takes the form of operations under the reformed Structural Funds (enjoying the priority given to the Objective 1 regions), but must also ensure that the special constraints affecting the Azores and Madeira are taken into account in the application of common policies, in accordance with the Community approach to the remoter regions, of which the adoption and implementation of the Poseidom programme for the French overseas departments is the first practical example; </inglise>
<eesti> Assooride ja Madeira t&otilde;sist strukturaalset mahaj&auml;&auml;must raskendavate piirangute (kaugus, eraldatus, v&auml;iksus, halvad maastiku- ja ilmastikuolud) muutumatu iseloom ja &uuml;hine m&otilde;ju raskendavad t&otilde;siselt majanduslikku ja sotsiaalset arengut, mille tulemusena on nende kahe saarestiku n&auml;ol tegemist &uuml;henduse ebasoodsaimate piirkondadega; need erilised piirangud muudavad vajalikuks suurendada &uuml;henduse abi, et kaasata Assoorid ja Madeira t&auml;ielikult siseturu d&uuml;naamilisse arengusse; &uuml;henduse abi antakse reformitud struktuurifondide kaudu (vastavalt eesm&auml;rgi nr 1 piirkondade eelistele), kuid see peab samuti tagama, et &uuml;histe poliitikate kohaldamisel arvestatakse Assoore ja Madeirat m&otilde;jutavaid erilisi piiranguid vastavalt &uuml;henduse poliitikale k&otilde;rvalisemate piirkondade suhtes, millest Poseidom-programmi vastuv&otilde;tmine ja rakendamine Prantsuse &uuml;lemeredepartemangude suhtes on esimene praktiline n&auml;ide; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas an overall, multi-sector approach is necessary to allow for the special constraints on the Azores and Madeira in the application of common policies; whereas a coherent line must be taken as part of an overall action programme involving legislative measures and financial commitments; </inglise>
<eesti> Assooride ja Madeira eriliste piirangute arvestamine &uuml;histe poliitikate kohaldamisel eeldab terviklikku, mitmeid sektoreid h&otilde;lmavat l&auml;henemist; &uuml;ldise tegevusprogrammi osana tuleb kohaldada &uuml;htset strateegiat, mis sisaldab seadusandlikke meetmeid ja rahalisi kohustusi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for the purposes of implementing this programme, the necessary legal acts will be adopted either by the Council or by the Commission, as appropriate, before 31 December 1992; whereas the application of certain measures in this programme could extend beyond the process of completing the internal market, given the permanent constraints which are a particular feature of the Azores and Madeira; </inglise>
<eesti> selle programmi rakendamiseks v&otilde;tab n&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;i komisjon vastu vajalikud &otilde;igusaktid enne 31. detsembrit 1992; arvestades piirangute p&uuml;sivust, mis on Assooride ja Madeira erip&auml;ra, v&otilde;ib selle programmi teatavate meetmete kohaldamine pikeneda p&auml;rast siseturu l&otilde;plikku moodustamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this programme must be based on the twofold principle that the Azores and Madeira form an integral part of the Community and that the regional reality deriving from their particular geographical situation must be recognized; </inglise>
<eesti> selle programmi l&auml;htepunktiks on p&otilde;him&otilde;te, et Assoorid ja Madeira on &uuml;henduse lahutamatu osa ja et nende erip&auml;rasest geograafilisest asendist tulenevaid piirkondlikke tingimusi tuleb aktsepteerida; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures contained in the programme must accordingly take into account the special characteristics and constraints of the Azores and Madeira without undermining the integrity and coherence of the Community legal order; whereas the economic effects of specific measures must therefore remain limited to the territory of the Azores and Madeira without affecting directly the functioning of the common market; </inglise>
<eesti> programmis sisalduvad meetmed peavad arvestama Assooride ja Madeira erijooni ja piiranguid, kahjustamata &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguskorra terviklikkust ja t&auml;ielikkust; erimeetmete majanduslik m&otilde;ju peab seet&otilde;ttu piirduma Assooride ja Madeira territooriumiga, ilma et see m&otilde;jutaks otseselt &uuml;histuru toimimist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Community policies already provide many instruments and programmes which could deal with some of the specific problems and constraints of the Azores and Madeira, notably concerning fisheries, energy, environment, the craft industry and research and development; whereas steps should be taken to put these instruments and programmes to best use in the Azores and Madeira, especially by ensuring that they reach these remote regions and by developing appropriate technical assistance measures; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;henduse poliitikatega on juba s&auml;testatud mitmeid vahendeid ja programme, mille abil saab tegeleda m&otilde;ne Assooride ja Madeira eriprobleemi ja piiranguga, eelk&otilde;ige kalanduse, energeetika, keskkonnakaitse, k&auml;sit&ouml;&ouml;nduse ning uurimis- ja arendustegevuse vallas; tuleks astuda samme nende vahendite ja programmide parimaks rakendamiseks Assooride ja Madeira suhtes, eelk&otilde;ige tagades nende leviku sealsetes kaugemates piirkondades ja arendades sobivaid tehnilise abi meetmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Community rules must take account of the specific nature of the Azores and Madeira and encourage their economic and social development, particularly in those areas where the fragile nature of island territories is particularly acute, such as transport, fisheries, taxation, the social sector, research and development, or the protection of the environment in view of the vulnerability of the Azores and Madeira to the risks of environmental or natural disasters; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;henduse eeskirjad peavad arvestama Assooride ja Madeira erijooni ja edendama nende majanduslikku ja sotsiaalset arengut, eelk&otilde;ige valdkondades, kus saarte &otilde;rn loodus on eriti kergesti haavatav, nagu transport, kalandus, maksustamine, sotsiaalsektor, uurimis- ja arendustegevus v&otilde;i keskkonnakaitse, arvestades Assooride ja Madeira haavatavust keskkonnariskide ja keskkonnakatastroofide puhul; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, with respect to taxation, the special characteristics of the Azores and Madeira can be catered for by allowing special indirect taxation arrangements compatible with the rules of the Treaty and capable of promoting their economic and social development; </inglise>
<eesti> maksustamisel saab Assooride ja Madeira erijooni arvestades lubada kaudse maksustamise erikorda, mis on koosk&otilde;las asutamislepingu eeskirjadega ja mille abil saab edendada majanduslikku ja sotsiaalset arengut; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is important, within the framework of the common transport policy guidelines, to provide regular transport links at the lowest possible cost to alleviate the drawbacks of remoteness and the island location; whereas air transport is an instrument of regional development and the most appropriate forms of greater liberalization should be sought, notably under partnership arrangements; </inglise>
<eesti> on oluline pakkuda &uuml;hise transpordipoliitika suuniste raames v&otilde;imalikult odavaid regulaarseid transporditeenuseid, et leevendada saarte asukohast tulenevaid puudusi; &otilde;hutransport on regionaalarengu edendamise vahend ja partnerlusp&otilde;him&otilde;ttest l&auml;htudes tuleks uurida, millised on liberaliseerimine sobivaimad viisid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the exceptional geographical situation of the Azores and Madeira in relation to sources of supply for products used as inputs in certain food sectors, which are essential for current consumption or processing in the two archipelagos, entails costs that are a severe handicap for these sectors; whereas there is a need, in this connection, to make special arrangements for the supply of these products within the limits of market needs for the two archipelagos in question and taking account of local production and traditional trade flows; </inglise>
<eesti> Assooride ja Madeira erandlik geograafiline asend teatavate kahe saarestiku tarbimis- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisvajaduste rahuldamiseks h&auml;davajalike toiduainetesektorite toodete tarneallikate suhtes p&otilde;hjustab kulutusi, mis seavad k&otilde;nealused sektorid t&otilde;sisesse halvemusse; seoses sellega on vaja kehtestada erikord nende toodete tarnimiseks turuvajaduste piires kahele k&otilde;nealusele saarestikule, v&otilde;ttes arvesse kohalikku toodangut ja tavap&auml;raseid kaubavoogusid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the extreme remoteness of the Azores and Madeira in relation to sources of supply of refined petroleum products, coupled with the heavy reliance on these products to meet energy needs and the compartmentalization of the market, means that supply costs in the Azores and Madeira are much higher than in mainland Portugal; whereas these costs are at present borne by the regional budgets, which limits correspondingly their capability for action to promote economic and social development; whereas these higher costs should be offset by temporary Community aid tied to the application by the two regions of incentive programmes to promote investment in energy saving and the development of local, renewable energy sources to improve the energy supply and demand situation on these islands; </inglise>
<eesti> Assooride ja Madeira kaugus rafineeritud naftasaaduste hankimisallikate suhtes ja nende saaduste h&auml;davajalikkus energiavajaduste rahuldamiseks koos turu killustatusega p&otilde;hjustavad selle, et tarnekulud Assooridel ja Madeiral on tunduvalt k&otilde;rgemad kui Portugali mandriosas; praegu kaetakse need kulud kohalikest eelarvetest, mist&otilde;ttu on vastavalt raskem soodustada majanduslikku ja sotsiaalset arengut; neid k&otilde;rgemaid kulutusi saaks kompenseerida &uuml;henduse ajutise abiga tingimusel, et asjaomased piirkonnad rakendavad programme, mis soodustavad investeeringuid energia s&auml;&auml;stmisse ja kohalike taastuvate energiaallikate arendamisse, et parandada energia pakkumise ja n&otilde;udmise olukorda k&otilde;nealustel saartel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas free zones can be an appreciable instrument of economic development in the remote island regions of the Azores and Madeira; whereas customs measures may be appropriate regarding the arrangements applicable to the free zones in the Azores and Madeira, in view of their special geographical situation; </inglise>
<eesti> vabatsoonid v&otilde;ivad olla Assooride ja Madeira kaugete saarepiirkondade majanduse arendamise t&otilde;hus vahend; arvestades nende erilist geograafilist asendit, v&otilde;ib Assooride ja Madeira vabatsoonides kehtiva korra suhtes olla vaja v&otilde;tta tollimeetmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the dependence of the Azores and Madeira on the outside world for supplies of steel products justifies special attention being paid to ensure that fair prices may be maintained for the products in question in the two archipelagos; </inglise>
<eesti> Assooride ja Madeira s&otilde;ltuvuse t&otilde;ttu v&auml;lismaailmast terasetoodete tarnimise puhul, tuleks p&ouml;&ouml;rata erilist t&auml;helepanu kahes saarestikus asjaomaste toodete soodsate hindade tagamisele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the special production conditions in the Azores and Madeira require that particular attention be paid to applying the common agricultural policy to this region; whereas appropriate measures are needed to assist the development of the fruit and vegetable and flowers and live plant sectors; whereas these measures will have to promote the growing of tropical products in particular; whereas special attention will have to be given to Madeira bananas in view of their crucial economic and social importance for the island and with due account for aspects relating to ecological balance and the countryside; whereas other market and structural measures will also be required to support these traditional products, in view of the overwhelming importance of the milk sector in the economic activity of the Azores and its role, which is difficult to replace, as a factor in maintaining the working population in the archipelago; </inglise>
<eesti> Assooride ja Madeira eriliste tootmistingimuste t&otilde;ttu on vaja p&ouml;&ouml;rata erilist t&auml;helepanu &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika kohaldamisele selles piirkonnas; on vaja asjakohaseid meetmeid, et aidata kaasa puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljasektori ning lillede ja elustaimede sektori arengule; need meetmed peavad eelk&otilde;ige soodustama troopikasaaduste kasvatamist; erilist t&auml;helepanu tuleb p&ouml;&ouml;rata Madeira banaanidele, arvestades nende olulist majanduslikku ja sotsiaalset t&auml;htsust saarel, v&otilde;ttes samas arvesse &ouml;koloogilist tasakaalu ja maastikukaitset; arvestades piimasektori suurt t&auml;htsust Assooride majanduses ja selle asendamatut osa t&ouml;&ouml;tava elanikkonna s&auml;ilitamisel saarestikus, on traditsioonilise tootmise toetamiseks vaja ka muid turu- ja struktuurimeetmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary to take measures in the fisheries sector in view of its economic and social importance for the two archipelagos; </inglise>
<eesti> on vaja v&otilde;tta meetmeid kalandussektori suhtes, arvestades selle majanduslikku ja sotsiaalset t&auml;htsust kahe saarestiku jaoks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in view of the considerable social importance of maintaining craft activities in the two regions, specific Community measures should be taken to fit in with those already planned under the Community support framework; whereas these measures should aim at promoting vocational training, access to new technology and the use of such technology, and access to new markets; </inglise>
<eesti> arvestades k&auml;sit&ouml;&ouml;nduse s&auml;ilitamise sotsiaalset t&auml;htsust neis kahes piirkonnas, tuleks v&otilde;tta selliseid &uuml;henduse erimeetmeid, mis sobiksid kokku &uuml;henduse abi raames juba planeeritud meetmetega; nende meetmete eesm&auml;rk peaks olema t&ouml;&ouml;alase koolituse edendamine, juurdep&auml;&auml;s uutele tehnoloogiatele ja nende kasutuselev&otilde;tt ning juurdep&auml;&auml;s uutele turgudele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the preparation, implementation, monitoring and evaluation of the measures provided for in this programme require a partnership between the Commission and the competent national and regional authorities; whereas this partnership must permit complementarity between the measures laid down in the programme and those applied at national and regional level; </inglise>
<eesti> selle programmiga etten&auml;htud meetmete ettevalmistamiseks, rakendamiseks, j&auml;relevalveks ja hindamiseks on vaja komisjoni ning p&auml;devate riiklike v&otilde;i piirkondlike asutuste koost&ouml;&ouml;d; see koost&ouml;&ouml; peab v&otilde;imaldama programmis s&auml;testatud meetmete ning riiklikul ja piirkondlikul tasandil rakendatud meetmete vastastikust t&auml;iendavust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Portugal and the regions concerned must take account of the measures and operations under this programme in drafting future regional development plans; whereas the Commission, within the scope of its powers, will take steps to ensure that this programme is consistent with the operations of the Structural Funds and other Community financial instruments, </inglise>
<eesti> Portugal ja asjaomased piirkonnad peavad tulevaste piirkondlike arengukavade koostamisel v&otilde;tma arvesse k&auml;esoleva programmi meetmeid ja toiminguid; komisjon astub oma p&auml;devuse piires samme, et tagada k&auml;esoleva programmi vastavus struktuurifondide ja &uuml;henduse muude finantsvahenditega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS DECIDED AS FOLLOWS: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD J&Auml;RGMISE OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> An action programme for Madeira and the Azores, known as Poseima (Programme of options specific to the remote and insular nature of Madeira and the Azores) and set out in the Annex, is hereby established. </inglise>
<eesti> Kehtestatakse Madeira ja Assooride tegevuskava Poseima (Assooride ja Madeira k&otilde;rvalisele asukohale ning saarelisele asendile vastavate valikmeetmete programm), mis on s&auml;testatud k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse lisas. </eesti>
<inglise> This programme shall cover regulatory measures and financial commitments. </inglise>
<eesti> See programm h&otilde;lmab reguleerivaid meetmeid ja rahalisi kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Within the context of the powers conferred upon it by the Treaty, the Council shall adopt the provisions necessary for the execution of this programme and invite the Commission to submit the relevant proposals as soon as possible. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;tab talle asutamislepinguga antud volituste raames vastu selle programmi teostamiseks vajalikud s&auml;tted ja kutsub komisjoni &uuml;les esitama v&otilde;imalikult kiiresti asjakohaseid ettepanekuid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The financial resources required to implement the measures relating to agricultural structures, energy and the craft industry appearing in this programme shall be determined in the annual budgetary procedures. </inglise>
<eesti> P&otilde;llumajandusstruktuuride, energeetika ja k&auml;sit&ouml;&ouml;ndusega seotud ja selles programmis nimetatud meetmete rakendamise rahalised vahendid m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks iga-aastase eelarvemenetluse raames. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision shall take effect on 1 July 1991. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus j&otilde;ustub 1. juulil 1991. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision shall be published in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus avaldatakse Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
